"title": "1466: vision",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1466: vision",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Scripture uses the term to refer to both the physical act of seeing, and also the gift of spiritual insight. All things, physical and spiritual, are seen by God.</p>\n<h2>God's vision</h2>\n<h3>God views all life on earth</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr16:9\">2CH 16:9</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps11:4\">PSA 11:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:11\">GEN 6:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:9\">EXO 3:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps31:22\">PSA 31:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps34:15\">PSA 34:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps139:16\">PSA 139:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech4:10\">ZEC 4:10</a></p>\n<h3>God sees the hearts and thoughts of people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:5\">GEN 6:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:3\">1SA 2:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps139:1-Ps139:4\">PSA 139:1–139:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps139:23-Ps139:24\">PSA 139:23–139:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov15:11\">PRO 15:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer20:12\">JER 20:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:8\">MAT 6:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:18\">MAT 6:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:15\">LUK 16:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:13\">HEB 4:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:20\">1JN 3:20</a></p>\n<h2>The physical vision of human beings</h2>\n<h3>It is given and can be taken by God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod4:11\">EXO 4:11</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps146:8\">PSA 146:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:16\">LEV 26:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov29:13\">PRO 29:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:8-Acts9:9\">ACT 9:8–9:9</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts22:11\">ACT 22:11</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ restores the sight of the blind</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:18\">LUK 4:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:30\">MAT 9:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:7\">JHN 9:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:17-Acts9:18\">ACT 9:17–9:18</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts22:13\">ACT 22:13</a></p>\n<h3>Physical sight diminishes with age</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:1\">GEN 27:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen48:10\">GEN 48:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam3:2\">1SA 3:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam4:15\">1SA 4:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs14:4\">1KI 14:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl12:3\">ECC 12:3</a> <em><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl12:2-Eccl12:5\">Ecc 12:2–5</a> is an allegory on ageing. It gives a graphic description of a person's progressive deterioration.</em></p>\n<h2>Physical vision has its dangers</h2>\n<h3>It can create fear</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job41:9\">JOB 41:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:6\">JOL 2:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:3-Matt28:4\">MAT 28:3–28:4</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:5\">MRK 16:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:4-Luke24:5\">LUK 24:4–24:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:17\">REV 1:17</a></p>\n<h3>It gives rise to temptation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:16\">1JN 2:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:6\">GEN 3:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:21\">JOS 7:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam11:2-2Sam11:4\">2SA 11:2–11:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job31:1\">JOB 31:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:37\">PSA 119:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:28-Matt5:29\">MAT 5:28–5:29</a></p>\n<h2>Christians are to live by faith rather than by sight</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:1\">HEB 11:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:24\">ROM 8:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:18\">2CO 4:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:7\">2CO 5:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:27\">HEB 11:27</a></p>\n<h2>Visions of God</h2>\n<h3>Examples of those who saw God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen32:30\">GEN 32:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:18-Exod33:23\">EXO 33:18–33:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job42:5\">JOB 42:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:1\">ISA 6:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:5\">ISA 6:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:12-Rev1:18\">REV 1:12–1:18</a></p>\n<h3>God's people will see him</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:8\">MAT 5:8</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:2\">1JN 3:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps17:15\">PSA 17:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:24\">JHN 17:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor13:12\">1CO 13:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:4\">REV 22:4</a></p>\n<h2>Spiritual vision</h2>\n<h3>Seeing used metaphorically for spiritual insight</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs6:17\">2KI 6:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov29:18\">PRO 29:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa22:1\">ISA 22:1</a> <em>Jerusalem was called “the Valley of Vision”, possibly ironically, for although God spoke through his prophets and dwelt there, its inhabitants lacked insight</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa29:10\">ISA 29:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:17-Mark8:21\">MRK 8:17–8:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:31\">LUK 24:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:39\">JHN 9:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:17-Acts26:18\">ACT 26:17–26:18</a></p>\n<h3>Spiritual insight given in dreams or visions</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:17\">ACT 2:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:28\">JOL 2:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:1\">GEN 15:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num12:6\">NUM 12:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan1:17\">DAN 1:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:19\">DAN 2:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:5\">DAN 4:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:1\">DAN 7:1</a> <em>Daniel's dream of four beasts</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan8:1\">DAN 8:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan10:7-Dan10:8\">DAN 10:7–10:8</a> <em>Daniel's vision of a man</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:12\">ACT 9:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:9-Acts10:17\">ACT 10:9–10:17</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:4-Acts11:10\">ACT 11:4–11:10</a> <em>Peter's vision</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:9-Acts16:10\">ACT 16:9–16:10</a> <em>Paul's vision of the man of Macedonia</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:19\">ACT 26:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:1\">2CO 12:1</a></p>\n<h3>The OT prophets had visions from God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam3:15\">1SA 3:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:1\">ISA 1:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer24:1\">JER 24:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek1:1\">EZK 1:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek8:3-Ezek8:4\">EZK 8:3–8:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek11:24\">EZK 11:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:2-Ezek40:3\">EZK 40:2–40:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos12:10\">HOS 12:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Obad1:1\">OBA 1:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah1:1\">NAM 1:1</a></p>\n<h3>False prophets in the OT lacked true vision</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer14:14\">JER 14:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:16\">JER 23:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam2:14\">LAM 2:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek7:26\">EZK 7:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek13:1-Ezek13:12\">EZK 13:1–13:12</a></p>",
